vel. The mean is 0.100896, and the stdDev is 0.067461 .","key":"K4PBOloTeZ","urlSource":"images/9_1_img1.gif"},{"type":"caption","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":66,"column":1},"end":{"line":66,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A set of sampling distributions and tables for N=20, 50, 100, and 200 . For each sample size, 1005 samples were taken. For N=200, the resulting distribution histogram very closely resembles a normal shape. The mean is 0.100095, and the stdDev is 0.0221608 . For N=100, the distribution histogram is also an approximation of a normal curve. Since the scale for this histogram is the same as for N=200, the bars are wider. The mean is 0.100557, and the stdDev is 0.0287191 . For N=50, the histogram has even wider bars. The left part of the normal curve has been cut off because it rests below a proportion of 0, which cannot happen. So, the histogram is right skewed. The mean is 0.102706, and the stdDdev is 0.0418382 . For N=20, the histogram suffers the same problem as for N=50, except on a much worse level. The mean is 0.100896, and the stdDev is 0.067461 .","position":{"start":{"line":66,"column":1},"end":{"line":66,"column":1}},"key":"ZMDn6TYbJL"}],"key":"JcYjnYG3xZ"}],"key":"OUlV0oxJmk"}],"enumerator":"1","key":"rk59wbpZZg"},{"type":"admonition","kind":"note","children":[{"type":"admonitionTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Note","key":"MXF8T4cXxo"}],"key":"I0Rhi0j4RF"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"**Sectionnest**\n\n*(Interactive activity — available in the OLI platform)*","position":{"start":{"line":70,"column":1},"end":{"line":72,"column":1}},"key":"AooWzetlfx"}],"key":"hpyu0sBl4F"}],"key":"cm59PTHpQK"}],"key":"mhSAVpT4Lk"},"references":{"cite":{"order":[],"data":{}}},"footer":{"navigation":{"prev":{"title":"Behavior of Sample Proportion (1 of 3)","url":"/pages/m12-behavior-of-sample-proportion-1-of-3","group":"Unit 4: Probability"},"next":{"title":"Behavior of Sample Proportion (3 of 3)",